definition.value: An academic degree in the science and principles of nursing, granted by an accredited tertiary education provider after the successful completion of a bachelor's of nursing program.
An academic degree granted by an accredited tertiary education provider after the successful completion of an associate of nursing program.

label.value: master's in the science of nursing degree

definition.value: An academic degree in the science and principles of nursing, granted by an accredited tertiary education provider after the successful completion of a master's of nursing program.
An objective specification that describes the endpoint of processes to  maintain competency and learn new and developing areas in trauma medicine.

Note that these are represented in OOST merely to define continuing trauma education plan specifications. 
(JB & MB 29 June 2017)
A plan specification that has a continuing trauma education objective specification as parts.

A physician role borne by a human being and that, if realized, is being realized by its bearer using operative manual and instrumental techniques on a patient to investigate or treat a pathological condition such as disease or injury, to help improve bodily function or appearance or to repair unwanted ruptured areas.
term requested in OMRSE. Do not use outside the CAFE application!

A surgeon role borne by a human being and, that, if realized, is realized by its bearer using operative manual or instrumental techniques on the musculoskeletal system of a patient to investigate or treat a pathological condition such as disease or injury, to help improve bodily function or appearance or to repair unwanted ruptured areas.
term requested in OMRSE. Do not use outside the CAFE application!

A physician role borne by a human being and that, if realized, is being realized by its bearer using operative manual and instrumental techniques on preadult patients to investigate or treat a pathological condition such as disease or injury, to help improve bodily function or appearance or to repair unwanted ruptured areas.
term requested in OMRSE. Do not use outside the CAFE application!
An organization that provides prehospital care or transport to the sick and wounded.

This term class is different from http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ARG_2000136 (emergency medical services). The latter seems to be inteded to represent a medical speciality, while this class represents an organization.

label.value: medical direction to emergency medical services

definition.value: A planned process that involves a physiscian and an agency providing prehospital care or transport of the sick and wounded and the physisican provides input regarding patient care and planning and operation of the service from a medical perspective.
A plan specification that specifies how the organizational structures interact to coordinate, manage and provide trauma care in a specified geographical region.

label.value: trauma quality improvement and patient safety program lead role

definition.value: A healthcare provider role that, if realized, is realized by planning, organizing and overseeing planned processes that realize the concretization of a trauma quality improvement and patient safety program.

A surgeon role borne by a human being and, that, if realized, is realized by its bearer using operative and non-operative manual or instrumental techniques on a patient to investigate or treat an injury or other pathological situation that are caused by an injury, to help improve bodily function or appearance or to repair unwanted ruptured areas.

A role that, if realized, is realized by its bearer providing an assessment of  processes carried out by another entity (person, organization, computer system) regarding their compliance with specifications and their quality.

A role that, if realized, is realized by its bearer undergoing an assessment of  its actions carried out by a person or an organization regarding the compliance with specifications and the quality of those actions.

label.value: authority to specify criteria for trauma service membership

definition.value: A deontic role that, if realized, is realized by its bearer providing a document that lists the minimum qualifications of a person to become a member of the trauma service.
A socio-legal generically dependent continuant that is concretized in a role within an organizational context and which legally, normatively, or ethically permits some action.
Authority prescribed by some enabling legislation

label.value: authority to appoint members to the trauma service

definition.value: A deontic role that, if realized, is realized by its bearer actively participating in a document act that has a trauma service member role as its specified output.

label.value: emergency medical services base station role

definition.value: An organization healthcare role that is borne by a hospital and that, if realized, is realized by directly organizing and controlling prehospital providers.
A document that is about a trauma registrar role and specifies the extent of work and the rights and obligations that are associated with that role.

It is important to note that this is not the rights and obligations or the professional role itself. This is a descriptive information content entity, not a directive one or a conglomerate of socio=legal entities.

label.value: authority to remove members from the trauma service

definition.value: A deontic role that, if realized, is realized by its bearer participating in a document act that revokes a trauma service member role.
An obligee role that, if realized, is realized by its bearer participating in continuing trauma eduction for an amount of time specified in their program or country.

label.value: trauma education verifiable for continuing medical education requirement

definition.value: A planned process that is scattered over multiple temporal regions that fulfills an obligation for continuing medical education in the area of trauma care.
A role that is borne by a member of an emergency department that has been authorized by department leadership and that, if realized, is realized by its bearer representing the emergency department.
A plan specification that specifies which orthopedic surgeon to call,  if the primary on-call orthopedic surgeon is not available due to already taking care of other trauma patients.
A governmental organization that has the authority to create, amend, fund, and repeal laws.
An organization that is a part of some government.
Government is the means by which policy within a community are enforced, as well as the mechanism for determining the policy of the community.
the community may be local, regional, state, or national (Comment provided by J. Ball, N. Sanddal, S. Bowman) - 2017-07-18
An organization consisting of persons who bear committee member role where that organization is appointed by an organization or members of an organization to realize a role.
Dec 10, 2016: The definition originally stated that the committee was realizing a function. After review of the BFO definition of function I decided to change it to "role". M. Brochhausen
A committee whose function is to evaluate the system of care within a trauma center.
A role that inheres in a homo sapiens that, if realized, is realized by preparing, keeping, and overseeing records made in a register.
A role that, if realized, is realized in the organization context of a committee.
A disposition realized in process profiles that have participants the biological qualities of patients and the practices and instruments of medical professionals.
An organization whose purpose is to serve the goals of a particular profession or whose members bear roles within a single profession.
A medical residency in the medical speciality that focuses on the care for undifferentiated and unscheduled  patients with illnesses and injuries requiring immediate medical attention.

A medical residency in the medical specialty that focuses on using operative manual or instrumental techniques on the musculoskeletal system of a patient to investigate or treat a pathological condition such as disease or injury, to help improve bodily function or appearance or to repair unwanted ruptured areas.

A medical residency in the medical specialty that focuses on using operative manual and instrumental techniques on the nervous system of a patient to investigate or treat a pathological condition such as disease or injury, to help improve bodily function or appearance or to repair unwanted ruptured areas.
A continuous coverage policy to ensure availability of a general surgeon.
A plan specification that specifies which surgeon to call,  if the on-call trauma surgeons is not available due to already taking care of other trauma patients.
An organization with a specific responsibility that is a part of a larger organization with a specific responsibility.
This class does not contain governmental departments. Governmental department is to be found here: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OOSTT_00000274 MB, Jan 4, 2017

A department that is part of a healthcare provider organization and that specialzes in the care for undifferentiated and unscheduled  patients with illnesses and injuries requiring immediate medical attention.
A plan specification that specifies which neurosurgeon to call,  if the primary on-call neurosurgeon is not available due to already taking care of other trauma patients.
A neurosurgeon backup call schedule that has been approved by the trauma medical director.

A planned process in which a person, an aggregate of persons or an organization reviews a plan specification and decides whether or not the plan specification is appropriate to achieve its objective and whether it is congruent with pre-existing plans and procedures.

label.value: TMD-approved orthopedic surgeon backup call schedule

definition.value: A orthopedic surgeon backup call schedule that has been approved by the trauma medical director.

label.value: obsolete_emergency department nursing liaison of trauma program

definition.value: A role that inheres in a person, who is a member in a trauma program, and, if realized, is realized by acting us the contact point of the trauma program regarding nursing care in the emergency department.
A plan specification that specifies on which schedule and to which extent anesthesia services are provided within a healthcare provider organization.
A planned process that realizes the concretization of an anesthesia services availability plan specification.
A continuous coverage policy to ensure availability of an orthopedic surgeon.
